DEVELOPER MANUAL
DCS Vehicles Data API – Version 2.3
Introduction
This documentation provides specifications for DCS’ Vehicles Data API Service. This is revision 2.3 dated 03/13/2017.
The DCS Vehicle API provides access to vehicle information via the registered address or household address, the Vehicle
Identification Number (Vin) or the license plate number (Tag).
Version Changes
Updated missing fields for vehicle values in the VehicleDetail section and synchronized the version to the version of the
API.
System Requirements
These web services are implemented over HTTPS.
Security and Authentication
Given the protected and sensitive nature of data involved in this service, access is both encrypted and restricted. The
encryption of request and response data is protected at the transport layer via the HTTPS protocol. Authentication and
authorization is provided through the use of HTTP Basic Authentication. Using this protocol, an authorization header is
created with Account Number, User ID and Password encoded into a Base64 string and added into the Post request. The
account number is your assigned account number from DCS. The customer determines the username and password.
Transaction Request
Requests are made via a Post verb. The Vehicles API includes three request options: Household, VIN and Tag. All three
use the same response structures. The body of the request contains the either HouseholdVehiclesRequest,
VehicleVinRequest or VehicleTagRequest formatted data. URI’s are supplied below in the sample requests. The site
listed is a test site and will be provided once production transactions are approved. VehicleVin is not required in the
HouseholdVehiclesRequest request.
Contact Information
If you need assistance with Web Services, technical support is available between 8 am and 5 pm CST Monday through
Friday, except holidays.
Toll free: 800.299.3647
Email: xmlsupport@dcsinfosys.com
Request and Response Examples
Household Vehicles Sample Request
Method: POST
Path: https://ws.dcsinfosys.com:442/apidevV2.3/DcsSearchApi/HouseholdVehicles
Content Type: application/xml
Body:
<HouseholdVehiclesRequest>
<TransactionInfo>
<DepartmentId>Dept 1</DepartmentId>
<UserId>JamesBee</UserId>
<UserName>Jim User</UserName>
</TransactionInfo>
<SearchAddress>
<Address>8700 Collingwood</Address>
<City>Austin</City>
<State>TX</State>
<ZipCode>78748</ZipCode>
</SearchAddress>
<VehicleVins>
<VehicleVin>
<Vin>1R23GHES8BL512313</Vin>
</VehicleVin>
<VehicleVin>
<Vin>RR5A1GH28BL874221</Vin>
</VehicleVin>
</VehicleVins>
</HouseholdVehiclesRequest>
Vehicle Vin Sample Request
Method: POST
Path: https://ws.dcsinfosys.com:442/apidevV2.3/DcsSearchApi/VehicleVin
Content Type: application/xml
Body:
<VehicleVinRequest>
<TransactionInfo>
<DepartmentId>Dept 1</DepartmentId>
<UserId>JamesBee</UserId>
<UserName>Jim User</UserName>
</TransactionInfo>
<VehicleVins>
<VehicleVin>
<Vin>1R23GHES8BL512313</Vin>
</VehicleVin>
<VehicleVin>
<Vin>RR5A1GH28BL874221</Vin>
</VehicleVin>
</VehicleVins>
</VehicleVinRequest>
Vehicle Tag Sample Request
Method: POST
Path: https://ws.dcsinfosys.com:442/apidevV2.3/DcsSearchApi/VehicleTag
Content Type: application/xml
Body:
<VehicleTagRequest>
<TransactionInfo>
<DepartmentId>Dept 1</DepartmentId>
<UserId>JamesBee</UserId>
<UserName>Jim User</UserName>
</TransactionInfo>
<VehicleTags>
<VehicleTag>
<Tag>ABC123</Tag>
</VehicleTag>
<VehicleTag>
<Tag>CX3421</Tag>
</VehicleTag>
</VehicleTags>
</VehicleTagRequest>
